Interface AngstdData

All Known Subinterfaces:
SequenceI
All Known Implementing Classes:
Domain, DomainArrangement, Sequence
public interface AngstdData

An empty interface indicating objects which can be parsed out of a file. If a class implements this interface (for instance DomainArrangement) it becomes a valid return type for parsers which implement the DataReader interface. For details see AbstractDataReader.

Author:
Andreas Held
